Parliament, Wednesday, 17 October 2018 – Parliament's Portfolio Committee on Trade and Industry today called for comments on additional clauses with respect to the Performers’ Protection Amendment Bill. Committee Chairperson, Ms Joanmariae Fubbs, said the clauses on which further comments are requested are: Interested individuals and groups can forward written submissions on the additional clauses on the Bill to the committee by no later than Wednesday, 31 October 2018. The committee will consider these comments during it deliberations on the Bill. Written submissions should be forwarded to Mr André Hermans and Mr Tenda Madima, Committee Secretaries, via email at ahermans@parliament.gov.za or tmadima@parliament.gov.za respectively.  Please find the link to the Bill:
